First, let's calculate if the APR is 9% and is compounded quarterly. Since the period is every quarter and we're calculating an annual rate, we will divide the annual twelve months by the quarter three months.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Compounding period} &= \dfrac{12\text{ months}}{3\text{ months}}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{4}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, we will use the compounding period of 4.
